review-css-url-data-image-no-base64,CSS url() with a safe image MIME type but no base64 encoding — the content is plain-text HTML smuggled behind an image/png declaration.,malicious,data-uri-smuggling,img-src,code review P0 finding — isSafeImageDataUri missing base64 check,"<div style=""background: url(data:image/png,<svg/onload=alert(1)>)"">x</div>",<div>x</div>
review-img-src-external-https,Image element with an external HTTPS URL. The Power BI sandbox does not allow visuals to load external resources; only data: URIs are permitted for img src.,malicious,html-attribute,img-src,code review P1 finding — allowedSchemesByTag not enforced,"<img src=""https://attacker.example/tracking.png"" alt=""x"">","<img alt=""x"">"
